<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/939.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-14">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Groups’ loan discussion is progressing rapidly. You will impress
                                emphatically upon Chinese Government that any hasty action by China
                                inconsistent with the large plans now pending would be most
                                unfortunate and would not be justified by a few days delay in the
                                next preliminary advance. This is most important.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>